Method Detail

isContentEqual

public static boolean isContentEqual(java.util.Collection<?> collectionA,
                                     java.util.Collection<?> collectionB)
Method checks if the given collections contain the same content. Please note that the method only check if each item of one collection is contained at least one times in the other collection. Method does not check if the number of containments of each element are equal. For example this means that { A , B , B } and { A , A , B } are contained equal content.

Parameters:
collectionA - the first collection
collectionB - the other collection
Returns:
true if the content are equal, false otherwise.

Parameters:

Returns:

asTwoDimension

public static final java.util.Collection<?> asTwoDimension(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object> obj)
Method reduces the given collection to a real two dimensional collection. In meaning, if the collection contains other collections, their content will be added. If this content is also a collection, it will be added its content too, a.s.o.

Parameters:
obj - the collection
Returns:
the new collection
